article.headline: Long Beach St. 71, San Francisco 68
article.story: EDS: Long Beach St. 71, San Francisco 68. LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) -- Donavan Morris scored a career-high 26 points and Long Beach State beat San Francisco 71-68 on Tuesday night. Morris was 9-of-14 from the field and 7-of-8 from free throw line and pulled down seven rebounds. His two free throws with 20 seconds remaining gave the 49ers a 71-68 lead. The Dons moved the ball down court for a last shot but Dior Lowhorn's attempt was off the mark. Maurice Clady rebounded the ball for Long Beach State as the game ended. San Francisco (4-7) dropped to 0-5 on the road and has lost all four games they have played this season against Big West opponents. Long Beach State (3-6) improved to 3-1 at home. Darnell Porter scored a career-high 18 points for the 49ers, who shot 55.6 percent (25-for-45) for the game. Manny Quezada, who fouled out with 20 seconds remaining, and Myron Strong both scored 18 points for the Dons while Lowhorn added 14.
